<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="480" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10901.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Russian Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-09"><hi rend="italic">January 9,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 60.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 6th instant, in which you request the
                            extradition of Jan Janoy Pouren, alias W. Kohks, alias Martin Martinson,
                            charged in Russia with the crimes of murder, robbery and attempted
                            murder.</p>
                        <pb facs="0587" n="515" xml:id="pg_515"/>
                        <p>I have the honor to say in reply that when the forms of law shall have
                            been complied with the department will issue a warrant for the surrender
                            of the accused.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>